# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback.
# The standalone build (src/main.tsx) uses BrowserRouter with real paths
# (/search, /countries/:code, …), so any deep link / refresh must serve
# index.html and let the client router resolve the route. Vite copies this
# file from public/ to dist/, where Cloudflare Pages reads it.
# (Replaces the old vercel.json rewrite — Cloudflare ignores vercel.json.)
# Missing /assets/* files are carved out of this fallback by the Pages Function
# functions/assets/[[path]].js — a hashed chunk from a superseded deployment
# must 404 (browsers reject index.html-as-module with a MIME error, and CDNs
# would cache the HTML under the asset URL). `_redirects` itself can't express
# an exclusion or a 404 status, hence the function.
